---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Private Poker Night - Optional Game Variations" description="Learn about optional game variations for our private poker night event">
<div class="bg-base-100 rounded-box p-6 shadow-lg mb-8">
    <div class="bg-white/50 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Optional Game Variations</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">To keep things interesting, the host ("The Princess") may introduce one of the following variations after the first game, at her discretion.</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">1. Progressive Ante</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">The ante increases by 1 point each round (e.g., 1 point in round 1, 2 points in round 2, etc.).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">2. House Collects Pot</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">The house collects the entire pot. The winner of the hand receives their initial bid back (not the ante).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">3. No Chips/Points</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">The player who loses a round directly loses a clothing article according to the removal order.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-100">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">4. Princess's Advantage</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-600">The host acts as the dealer with extra face-up cards, increasing her odds. If she wins, she chooses who removes an article of clothing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>